# Error Handling Rules

## Services
- ✅ Use AppError classes instead of raw exceptions
- ✅ Transform errors with errorHandler.handleFirebaseError()
- ✅ Add context (component, action) to all errors
- ✅ Use structured logging with logger.error()
- ✅ Implement retry logic for network operations
- ✅ React Query: Configure retry and error states

## UI Components
- ✅ Wrap components in ErrorBoundary hierarchy
- ✅ Use ErrorDisplay for user-facing errors
- ✅ Use ErrorToast for notifications
- ✅ Implement LoadingStates for better UX
- ✅ Provide retry mechanisms for critical operations
- ✅ Show user-friendly German error messages

## Error Boundaries
- ✅ GlobalErrorBoundary: Root-level error catching
- ✅ RouteErrorBoundary: Route-specific isolation
- ✅ ComponentErrorBoundary: Component-level isolation
- ✅ Use withComponentErrorBoundary HOC for easy wrapping

## Logging
- ✅ Use logger instead of console.log/error/warn
- ✅ Add context (userId, sessionId, route) to logs
- ✅ Use appropriate log levels (debug, info, warn, error, critical)
- ✅ Log performance metrics and user actions
- ✅ Production: Structured JSON logging ready

## Error Types
- ✅ Use typed ErrorCode enum for consistency
- ✅ Use ErrorSeverity levels (critical, error, warning, info)
- ✅ Provide German user messages for all errors
- ✅ Include technical details for debugging

## Testing
- ✅ Test error boundary behavior
- ✅ Test service error handling
- ✅ Test user error flows
- ✅ Mock error scenarios in tests

## Monitoring (Optional)
- ✅ Sentry integration prepared (feature-flagged)
- ✅ Error analytics foundation ready
- ✅ Performance monitoring hooks available
- ✅ Error grouping and fingerprinting

## Best Practices
- ✅ Never throw raw errors - always use AppError
- ✅ Always provide user-friendly error messages
- ✅ Include context for debugging
- ✅ Implement graceful degradation
- ✅ Provide recovery mechanisms
- ✅ Log errors with structured data

## Examples

### Service Error Handling
```typescript
try {
  const result = await firebaseOperation();
  return result;
} catch (error) {
  const appError = errorHandler.handleFirebaseError(error, {
    component: 'userService',
    action: 'getUserById'
  });
  logger.error('Failed to get user', appError, { userId: id });
  throw appError;
}
```

### Component Error Handling
```typescript
<ComponentErrorBoundary component="UserProfile">
  <UserProfileContent user={user} />
</ComponentErrorBoundary>
```

### Toast Notifications
```typescript
const { showSuccess, showError } = useToastManager();
showSuccess('Benutzer erfolgreich gespeichert!');
showError('Fehler beim Speichern');
```

### Loading States
```typescript
<LoadingState variant="skeleton" rows={3} />
<LoadingState variant="spinner" message="Lädt..." />
```

